<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-38-0862 </DOCNO><TEXT>The effect of granularity in powder X-ray diffraction is reviewed, andthe shortcomings of previously developed models in explaining this effectare described. A new physical model encompassing all aspects of thisphenomenon is proposed. Mathematical formulae based on the model arederived, and their limit cases are discussed. Values of the theoreticalintensities from the model are compared with results from a speciallydesigned experiment.</TEXT></DOC>